        "text": "Task Forces assigned as before. Task Force 17 sailed from San Diego for Samoa, date of arrival, 20th. The large, slow convoy (DETROIT) had been joined by the PORTLAND and two DD from Pearl. War Department infoted Commanding General that the u.s. participation in the construction of the air field at Noumea is his responsibility. Australia should defend New Caledonia, but u.s. may have to contribute.",
