        "text": ".\nAttacks by Task Forces 8 and 17 were successfullJ\ncarried out today except that heavy rain decreased the effectiveness of that agqinst Jaluit ..\nResults:\nDy rr. F. 17 Uakin - 1 auxiliary badly damaged, two\nseaplanes destroyed.\nJaluit - 1 out of two auxiliaries badly\ndamaced; no aircraft present.\nMili - Nothins present.\n(Seven of our airdraft lost).\nT.F. 17 retiring for fuel.\nBy T.P. 8 Kwajalein - many auxiliaries and aircraft\n~---- destroyed, some shore installations attacked.\nWotje Many auxiliaries destroyed,\nshore installations bombed and\nbombarded~\nMaloelap - Installations bombed and\nbombarded.\n(Six of our aircraft lost, CHESTZR hit by\nbomb amidships, ENTERPRISE some damage\nfrom near misses.. CliESTR can still make\nthirty knots).\nT .. F. 8 retiring toward Pearl in urgent need\nof fuel. T.F. 11 will meet him north of\nJohnston Island. T.F. 11 depaPted this\nmorning.\nHELM received attack at Baker Island from large seaplane -\n~{-c(t~~e~ n9 ,.~flmf,~~~-qt('t probably damaged plane. Co~ plc1e..d evct-vt :->~\nI1\\..SKASKIA vras told to resume voyage because PLJ TTE was\nnearing Pearl A Standard Oil tanker was being prepared for fuel-\nin2 at sea.\nCominch in 311606 directed that CinCPac control routing\nof Convoys 2030 and BT200, and also cover them with a carrier\ngroup operatlng in the South Pacific east of 1000. Convoy 2030\nsailed from S .. F .. today for Ca.nton, Chnistmas and Xray ..\nf~(\nThe enemy continues to advance in his offegsive. He is\nBS\ninstalled at Balikpapan and in southeast Celebe!J. , e has reache~ Johore Strait in !,~alaya ~ He may have landed at Salamoa, New\nGuinea and he is believed to be reconnoitering the Hew Hebrides ..\nHade detailed despatch report to Cominch as to composition and employment of task forces .\nAN. GCT",
