        "text": "At an informal conference held by the Conmander-in-Chief\ntoday the future employment of Task Poce 11 was discussed •\n.. 1 though 1 t had been planned to :b..a ve this force operate with\nTask Force One, chiefly in trainin~ exercises, it now ap,ears\nthat it would be Moro profitable for it to join Task Force\nSeventeen to oppose the enemy in his advance in the Hew Guinea-\nSolomon .area. Contrary to previous decision the LXHGTON is\nhavinc; her t:;ur1)ine repaired until about the 15th. \"'\"he chief\nmot ive. in having the battleships (Task Force One) put to sea for\na considerable period is to exert a diverting or holding effect\non enemy forces 1vhich night otherwise support the offensive in\nthe Indian Pocean.\nRear Admiral Bloch was detached as Comhawseafront.\nThe HRIGI-rr and TUCKER departed today in accordance with\nCinCPac 290241 (not attached). 'l,he KtSKASKIA was added to this\nexpedition to provide for fuel needs in the Anzac or Solonon Area.\nThe chief cargo of the WRIGHT is material for the patrol plane\nsquadron vhich has just been transferred to Fremantle but she is\nalso carrying miscellaneous itens to other bases.\nThere was received from Cominch 311840 which reversed\nthe previous interpretation of Secnav that CinCPac is the \"rlilitary\nCommander\" required to coordinate intelligence activities in\nHawaii. In reply 020247 was sent.\nThe expedition for the salvase of the ~AYLOR uas ordered\nby CinCPac 030125.\n'rhe POLLACE which na trolled in the East China Sea reports\nsinkine.; one freih-cer. rrh~ \"bae;\" by subnarines continues to be\nsMall but is causin~ the enemy concern and is diverting his\nforces for escorts.\nNo new trends were noted in eneny action. There is\nstill douht as vJhether ho has occup:.ed 3hortlancl Harbor, but a\nreliable r0port was received that about 500 troops had landed at\nBuK2 PasDace ·v1here there is a small airfield ..\n1.~-pril 3 ..\n~eceived Contaskfor lry plan for lis next operation\n020250 (Aidac)G Comtaskfor 17 has also issued orders for the\nService Force clotachm.e:nt to meet him at Bl.eacher on 1 May ..\nVice Admiral IIal sey has not yet returned, so that plans\nare still heing held up ..\n3 08\nMAR -G-CT-\n-·-",
